name: Push Up
description: A classic bodyweight exercise that targets the chest, shoulders, and triceps.

name: Pull Up
description: An upper-body strength exercise. The pull-up is a closed-chain movement where the body is suspended by the hands and pulls up.

name: Squat
description: A compound, full-body exercise that trains primarily the muscles of the thighs, hips and buttocks, quadriceps femoris muscle, hamstrings.

name: Deadlift
description: A weight training exercise in which a loaded barbell or bar is lifted off the ground to the level of the hips, torso perpendicular to the floor, before being placed back on the ground.

name: Bench Press
description: An upper-body weight training exercise in which the trainee presses a weight upwards while lying on a weight training bench.

name: Plank
description: An isometric core strength exercise that involves maintaining a position similar to a push-up for the maximum possible time.
